Makeup Moodle: Trust issues with Bloggers and Reviews Makeup Moodle: Trust issues with Bloggers and Reviews
Hello Everyone,
Today’s post is going to be very different from what I regularly post and I am sure not all of you would agree with me which is Okk.. It is not a sponsored post and is not about attacking someone or calling names. It is just about the things that are going on in my mind and share with you my views on it. I am venting out my opinion here but would love to have a sort of discussion with you people about the same.


Where to start from.. There are some perks of being a blogger like you get free products/samples from the brands to promote on your blog and also get invites to the events where they distribute goodies as a token of thanks and appreciation. Some brands also pay for reviewing their products on the blog which is perfectly fine with me. I am not against sponsored post or reviews and I myself have been associated with many brands in the past but do the bloggers actually mention it to their readers that they have been paid for that particular review or the product was sent by brand.
Many of them do but there are those who don’t and would love to get away with it without sharing the truth with their readers. I feel that’s ethically wrong and no matter what, blogger should mention it in the blog post itself about certain product been sent by brand or bought with her own money..
Now, the most important part of the story… Do they tell you the truth?? Do bloggers actually liked the product so much that they are giving it a high rating or it is just because they don’t want to spoil their relationship with the brands/PR. I am not naming any of the bloggers here ( because that will be too controversial and is actually not the purpose of this post) but I have myself experienced it.

There are so many products that I bought on blogger’s recommendation and reviews but they just failed to deliver on me.. and I am not talking about skin care here because that’s obvious that if one thing is working for some it wont work for other. I am talking only about makeup be it highlighters, eye shadows, liners, lipsticks ( chubby sticks), foundations and much more.
I hate it when I spend my hard earned money on some product based on review of a so call “Big Blogger” and it just refused to work on me. It is still fine that it is not working on me.. but why is it only me and nobody else in the whole blogging community that had a similar experience… literally no one!! Sayyy whatttt 
It is so hard to find a negative review on products especially if they are sent by brands.. I have been a victim of all those positive reviews so many times that I felt this issue needs to be addressed. Whether you are big blogger with huge following or just a beginner, it is your responsibility to not misguide others for your personal benefit.
The whole reason of us “Beauty bloggers” starting blogging was to share our experience with the products and not to work for some brands/ PR companies. We should be honest about what we are saying about the product whether or not it is sent by PR or are being paid for it.. always speak the truth because the readers trust our reviews and spend their hard earned money on the products we recommend..!!
Think again are you doing it the right way! Don’t be afraid of sharing your opinion even if it is not what others have to say. If you don’t like any product.. say itt!! It is okay if one product is not working for you the way it is on other but you shouldn’t be posting all the positive things about it just because nobody else is saying so or you fear that your relationship will be ruined with the brand and they will not send any more free products to you!
PS: If you want I can share the list of products that just didnt worked for me while the whole blogging community was going head over heels and recommending them.
Do share your thoughts in comments below and let me know what you guys think about this issue! 
I do not claim the ownership of the images used in this post!

Revlon Shadow Link Eye Shadows: They are hard as rock with poor pigmentation

MAC Potent Lip Polish: They were sticky like lip glosses.

WELLA : Partenaire Officiel du 57e Festival de Télévision de Monte-Carlo - Radio VL

WELLA : Partenaire Officiel du 57e Festival de Télévision de Monte-Carlo - Radio VL Pour la première fois, WELLA est Partenaire Officiel du Festival du Film de Télévision qui se déroulera à Monte-Carlo du 16 au 20 juin 2017. ... le tout placé sous le signe de l’élégance et du glamour !
 
Marque iconique du monde de la coiffure, WELLA se devait d’être présente lors de cette manifestation internationale, où se retrouveront des artistes parmi les plus célèbres du petit écran. Depuis 135 ans, WELLA développe des innovations et des services qui permettent aux coiffeurs de stimuler leur créativité.
 
 

 
Toujours à la pointe des tendances et des créations en matière de coloration, de soin et de coiffage, WELLA est le partenaire privilégié des coiffeurs pour révéler la beauté de tous les cheveux ! Des produits révolutionnaires conçus en ... les limites de la coiffure… un seul mot d’ordre : rien ne doit freiner l’audace et la créativité !
 
WELLA est l’une des marques de Coty, l’une des plus grandes entreprises de beauté au monde avec un chiffre d’affaires estimé ... mondial avec OPI dans les salons et numéro 2 mondial sur le marché capillaire professionnel avec des marques telles que WELLA Professionals, Sebastian Professional, System Professional et ghd.

いつもありがとう
#イルミナカラー
イルミナカラーは、痛まなく透明感が出ると今好評です。

当店では普通のカラー料金でやっています。

なぜかって?
まだ色味が少ないので、できる人とできない人がいるので、こちらで判断しできる方に、できるだけイルミナカラーに変更にしてる感じなので、料金は通常カラーと一緒です。

イルミナカラーは平均1万円が妥当と言いますが、当店ではロング6480円です。

髪が傷んでしまう原因にアプローチしながら、毛染めを行うことのできるイルミナカラーは髪が傷まない、新しいカラー剤と言われていて、イルミナカラーは普通のカラー剤の5倍髪が傷まないらしいです。
傷むからブリーチはしたくない!けど外人さんのような透明感のある髪になりたい!!っていう人にはいいと言われて今、Googleではかなりのヒット数

インスタでのハッシュタグでもものすごい数です。

色味ベースがブルーなので、アッシュやベージュに強いです。

ですが、デメリットとしてまだ、色が少ないこと、料金が高いこと、取扱店が少ない事がデメリットとしてあげられています。

当店では、#ウエラ を使っているので、髪の状態を見ながら、どちらのカラーで染めるのがいいかやっていますので、イルミナカラーやりたいという方は、ご相談くださいね。

1透明感があって外人風カラーのブリーチなしでも透明感が出ると、うたっています。

2髪が傷んでしまう原因にアプローチしながら、毛染めを行うことのできるイルミナカラーは髪が傷まない、新しいカラー剤と言われていて、イルミナカラーは普通のカラー剤の5倍髪が傷まないらしいです。
従来のカラー剤で1度のカラーをした場合の髪のダメージと、イルミナカラーを5回繰り返した際の髪のダメージがほぼ同じ髪の傷み具合だったらしいです。

EN LA COMPETENCIA WELLA TREND VISION AWARDS NORTEAMÉRICA 2017 Se eligieron los dos estilistas que representarán a Puerto Rico en la competencia internacional en ... industria de la peluquería, estilistas puertorriqueños dieron rienda suelta a sus habilidades artísticas durante la prestigiosa competencia por el premio Wella Trend Vision Award Norteamérica 2017, celebrada en Los Ángeles, California.  Durante esta competencia preliminar, un panel de jueces compuesto por ... a cabo en Londres el 14 de octubre de 2017.Inspirándose en las tendencias en color y estilo de cabello de Wella para las temporadas de Primavera/Verano 2017 y Otoño/Invierno 2017, los estilistas compitieron por los premios de Oro, Plata y Bronce ... expresar su creatividad para crear un look apropiado para un editorial de moda.De Puerto Rico, se alzaron con el premio Wella Trend Vision de Oro los estilistas José Quiñones de Peter Cardón Salon en la categoría de “Color Vision” y Glory ... y Puerto Rico en la categoría de “Estudiante”.Además de la oportunidad de representar a Puerto Rico en la competencia internacional Wella Trend Vision Award 2017, el ganador de la categoría de “Color Vision” recibió como premio una entrevista y sesión fotográfica ... la reconocida revista Vogue, mientras la ganadora de la categoría de “Creative Vision” tendrá un lugar en el equipo de Wella que participará en la Semana de la Moda en Nueva York.“Siempre había soñado con ganar esta competencia.  Fue una noche ... toda la fuerza para traer Oro a Puerto Rico”, dijo José Quiñones.  “Mi look fue inspirado en la colección de Wella llamada Optical Illusion.  Interpreté la ilusión óptica con una sombra en un canvas plano resultando en el efecto de un ... antiguas, hechas totalmente a mano”.   La estilista expresó además su orgullo y agradecimiento por haber participado y ganado el premio Wella Trend Vision Award: “Me siento sumamente orgullosa de todo el equipo de Puerto Rico, cualquiera pudo haber sido el ganador... ... junto con el gran orgullo de representar a mi patria en Londres, es mi recompensa por muchos años de trabajo”. Wella Trend Vision Awards Norteamérica 2017En la categoría de “Color Vision” de Puerto Rico, el premio de Plata fue para Ruth ... by Sheila; y Rafael Ortiz Cotto, de Rafael Ortiz Salón & Unisex Academy. Wellaplex, il colore dei sogni senza danni Dire sì al biondo ultra chiaro (o al nero intenso) ed essere certe che i capelli non usciranno dal trattamento colore danneggiati, anzi. Non è un’utopia, ma la nuova proposta Wellaplex di casa Wella.
Di cosa si tratta? Il team di professionisti Wella Professionals ha deciso di voler offrire un servizio a tutte quelle donne che desiderano modificare il proprio colore, senza però ... 50% delle donne che oggi non colora i capelli, vorrebbe farlo ma ha paura di danneggiarli.
Ed ecco la magia: Wellaplex è un sistema in tre fasi che consente di proteggere e rinforzare la chioma. Spieghiamo come ci riesce: i primi ... a No3 Hair Stabilizer, trattamento da fare una volta a settimana, fra un servizio colore a l’altro.
Il segreto di Wellaplex è racchiuso nella nuova tecnologia Opti pH System, un sistema di rigenerazione che durante il servizio colore penetra nella struttura ... decolorazione, colorazione, ondulazione, stiratura.
La costanza pagherà: capelli sani e vitali, colore sempre al top.

Here’s how to get the look.
“I started by applying Wella Eimi Full Volume Mousse through-out her wet hair and blow dried smooth with a round brush. Blow dry all the hair backwards lifting at the roots for extra volume.
Next add Wella Eimi Luminous Reflective Oil through- out the ends to add shine and smoothness and make the hair more manageable.
Spray Wella Eimi Dry Me throughout all the roots and leave for 5 minutes to absorb. Once the 5 minutes are up ... Shake out the waves with your fingers to add a tiny bit of texture and spray the entire hair with Wella Eimi Stay Firm hairspray for long lasting results.
